The following example [$merge](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/merge) syntax writes the results to a
`sampleDB.mySampleData` collection on the Atlas cluster named
`myTestCluster` in the background. The example doesn't specify a
project ID; the [$merge](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/merge) stage uses the ID of the project
that contains your federated database instance.

> **Example:**&#x20;
>
> ```json
> db.runCommand({
>   "aggregate": "mySampleData",
>   "pipeline": [
>     {
>       "$merge": {
>         "into": {
>           "atlas": {
>             "clusterName": "myTestCluster",
>             "db": "sampleDB",
>             "coll": "mySampleData"
>           }
>         },
>         ...
>       }
>     }
>   ],
>   { "background" : true }
> })
> ```
